variables.name: TYPE_VIEW_APPEARED
variables.comment:
* Called when a node has been added to the screen and is visible to the user. * *

The metadata of the node is available through {@link #getViewNode()}.

variables.name: TYPE_VIEW_DISAPPEARED
variables.comment:
* Called when one or more nodes have been removed from the screen and is not visible to the * user anymore. * *

To get the id(s), first call {@link #getIds()} - if it returns {@code null}, then call * {@link #getId()}.

variables.name: TYPE_VIEW_TEXT_CHANGED
variables.comment:
* Called when the text of a node has been changed. * *

The id of the node is available through {@link #getId()}, and the new text is * available through {@link #getText()}.

variables.name: TYPE_VIEW_TREE_APPEARING
variables.comment:
* Called before events (such as {@link #TYPE_VIEW_APPEARED} and/or * {@link #TYPE_VIEW_DISAPPEARED}) representing a view hierarchy are sent. * *

NOTE: there is no guarantee this event will be sent. For example, it's not sent * if the initial view hierarchy doesn't initially have any view that's important for content * capture.

variables.name: TYPE_VIEW_TREE_APPEARED
variables.comment:
* Called after events (such as {@link #TYPE_VIEW_APPEARED} and/or * {@link #TYPE_VIEW_DISAPPEARED}) representing a view hierarchy were sent. * *

NOTE: there is no guarantee this event will be sent. For example, it's not sent * if the initial view hierarchy doesn't initially have any view that's important for content * capture.

variables.name: TYPE_CONTEXT_UPDATED
variables.comment:
* Called after a call to * {@link ContentCaptureSession#setContentCaptureContext(ContentCaptureContext)}. * *

The passed context is available through {@link #getContentCaptureContext()}.

variables.name: TYPE_SESSION_RESUMED
variables.comment:
* Called after the session is ready, typically after the activity resumed and the
     * initial views appeared

variables.name: TYPE_SESSION_PAUSED
variables.comment:
* Called after the session is paused, typically after the activity paused and the
     * views disappeared.

variables.name: TYPE_VIEW_INSETS_CHANGED
variables.comment:
* Called when the view's insets are changed. The new insets associated with the
     * event may then be retrieved by calling {@link #getInsets()}

methods.name: public ContentCaptureEvent addAutofillId(@NonNull AutofillId id)
methods.comment:
* Adds an autofill id to the this event, merging the single id into a list if necessary.
     *
     * @hide

methods.name: public ContentCaptureContext getContentCaptureContext()
methods.comment:
* Gets the {@link ContentCaptureContext} set calls to * {@link ContentCaptureSession#setContentCaptureContext(ContentCaptureContext)}. * *

Only set on {@link #TYPE_CONTEXT_UPDATED} events.

methods.name: public int getType()
methods.comment:
* Gets the type of the event.
     *
     * @return one of {@link #TYPE_VIEW_APPEARED}, {@link #TYPE_VIEW_DISAPPEARED},
     * {@link #TYPE_VIEW_TEXT_CHANGED}, {@link #TYPE_VIEW_TREE_APPEARING},
     * {@link #TYPE_VIEW_TREE_APPEARED}, {@link #TYPE_CONTEXT_UPDATED},
     * {@link #TYPE_SESSION_RESUMED}, or {@link #TYPE_SESSION_PAUSED}.

methods.name: public long getEventTime()
methods.comment: * Gets when the event was generated, in millis since epoch.

methods.name: public ViewNode getViewNode()
methods.comment:
* Gets the whole metadata of the node associated with the event. * *

Only set on {@link #TYPE_VIEW_APPEARED} events.

methods.name: public AutofillId getId()
methods.comment:
* Gets the {@link AutofillId} of the node associated with the event. * *

Only set on {@link #TYPE_VIEW_DISAPPEARED} (when the event contains just one node - if * it contains more than one, this method returns {@code null} and the actual ids should be * retrived by {@link #getIds()}) and {@link #TYPE_VIEW_TEXT_CHANGED} events.

methods.name: public List<AutofillId> getIds()
methods.comment:
* Gets the {@link AutofillId AutofillIds} of the nodes associated with the event. * *

Only set on {@link #TYPE_VIEW_DISAPPEARED}, when the event contains more than one node * (if it contains just one node, it's returned by {@link #getId()} instead.

methods.name: public CharSequence getText()
methods.comment:
* Gets the current text of the node associated with the event. * *

Only set on {@link #TYPE_VIEW_TEXT_CHANGED} events.

methods.name: public Insets getInsets()
methods.comment:
* Gets the rectangle of the insets associated with the event. Valid insets will only be
     * returned if the type of the event is {@link #TYPE_VIEW_INSETS_CHANGED}, otherwise they
     * will be null.

methods.name: public void mergeEvent(@NonNull ContentCaptureEvent event)
methods.comment:
* Merges event of the same type, either {@link #TYPE_VIEW_TEXT_CHANGED}
     * or {@link #TYPE_VIEW_DISAPPEARED}.
     *
     * @hide
